column5: We were kind of trying to provide a little levity during the twilight of the cabin fever period. I reset it this morning. It seems that some folks are not into smirks and chuckles. Walleye, pickerel, dor√©..... it's called communication. As long as the people you're speaking to understand what you're talking about, there shouldn't be a problem. A rose by any other name... Hey, and it could have been worse. It could have been called by its true accepted name which is "zander". Look it up, it's been verified.  Smile, it's Friday, have a super day everyone!
Apology accepted.
I thought it was great fun Thanks to whatever mod pulled the prank.I enjoyed the levity.
Darn, I missed something again!!
hahaha I was wondering if it was still April 1st.
Scientific Name: Sander Vitreus; formally Stizostedion Vitreum.
I understand the intent behind the word play, but I guess one would have to have had their words (and meaning) changed without their consent, or knowledge, to understand the frustration.
Wow...lighten up...it's just the internet.
T'was a tasty little pranky....its time cut short by those who thought it stanky.
Quitt yer jumping on Roy.  ..IT WAS MY SUGGESTION AND IT WAS FUNNY!!!!!!   Have a little humour Newsman.   PS  Sorry Roy...you guys know you should never listen to me eh...
At the end of the day them there Yellow Pike are called "Good Eats" by everyone...
So I'm thinkin Roy if I said lets have a few pops or oat sodas----we're talkin the same lingo
DAMN YOU BIG BROTHER!!!!
